dlmanager is pretty straight forward. Open it in metaTower, add a torrent or nzb file to the queue, watch it download.
Usenet will be disabled unless you configure it, here's the template:

    <nzb>
        <server> SERVER_ADDRESS </server>
        <port> SERVER_PORT </port>
        <username> YOURUSERNAME </username>
        <ssl> true/false </ssl>
        <password> SERVER_PASS </password>
        <connections> 20 </connections>
        <save_to> files/downloads/nzb/ </save_to>
        <timeout> 15 </timeout>
        <unrar> /usr/bin/unrar </unrar>
        <par2> /usr/bin/par2 </par2>
    </nzb>

Make a copy of dlmanager.default.cfg, rename it to dlmanager.cfg and paste that into it within the <dlmanager> and </dlmanager> tags after you change the values to your own.
